# BUG-04 — Never LFS-track planning markdown. PITFALLS.md §15 (root cause #5).
.planning/**/*.md -lfs -filter -diff -merge -text

# Pin the corpus manifest to CRLF on every checkout. corpus_hash() in
# backend/cache/lineage.py is a raw sha256 of the file bytes and is baked into
# lineage.json + every cache_key, so a Windows-trained lineage (CRLF) cannot be
# validated against a Linux checkout (LF). Forcing CRLF everywhere keeps the
# hash platform-independent until corpus_hash() is itself normalized (v2.1).
corpus/books.yaml text eol=crlf
